    "# Exercise 2.10: Discrete sample spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "(a) We have $p(N) = \\big(\\frac{1}{100}\\big)\\big(\\frac{99}{100}\\big)^{N−1}$, for $N=1,2,...$. Since we observe $y = 203$, it follows that $N\\geq 203$. \n",
